  "The membrane potential reaches exactly zero millivolts": "",
  "Hyperpolarization occurs when the membrane potential dips below the resting potential (more negative than -70 mV), often due to excess K+ efflux, making the neuron temporarily less likely to reach threshold and fire.": "",
